Analysis.name: Blood transfusion
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: "Participants were randomly allocated (1:1). The randomization sequence was computer-generated in permuted blocks of varying sizes by a researcher not involved in data collection and imported into RedCap, an electronic tool for capturing research data. A research assistant did the randomisation, in the presence of the participant on the same day as the intervention, by clicking on a link in the RedCap system that generated the next sequential number according to central allocation”.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: ITT, PP, and as treated analysis reported with similar relative rates. Crossovers reported.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: Unblinded study but unlikely to have affected measurement of the outcome blood transfusion.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: All outcomes reported in the protocol also reported in the article. Minor changes made to protocol reported in the article.
Overall.bias.support: Low risk of bias across all domains

Analysis.name: Blood transfusion
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: No deviations from intended interventions in the interim data.
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: The study planned to include 1222 participants but there is only data on 123 participants .
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: Unblinded study but unlikely to have affected measurement of the outcome blood transfusion.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: Standard abortion care outcomes presented in methods and results.
Overall.bias.support: High risk of bias in one domain gives an overall high risk of bias

Analysis.name: Blood transfusion
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: “Women were randomized to either remote or clinic-based follow-up when a clinic research staff member opened the next sequential sealed opaque envelope indicating group assignment. The groups were created by Gynuity Health Projects using a computer-generated sequence in blocks of 8 and stratified by study site”.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: Large numbers of cross overs from the control group to the intervention group, which may have important implications for included outcomes. 279/337 (83%) in the in-clinic group were followed up over phone.
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Missing outcome data above 25% in both the intervention group and the control group.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: Unblinded study but unlikely to have affected measurement of the outcome blood transfusion.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: Standard abortion care outcomes presented in methods and results.
Overall.bias.support: High risk of bias in one or more domains gives an overall high risk of bias
